    "body": "## Purpose\nMemory profiling during startup doesn't account for all uses of GPU memory, hence the need for `--gpu-memory-utilization`. One notable miss is the size of the CUDA graphs, which are captured after memory profiling due to their dependence on the KV cache. This can lead to oversized KV cache and subsequent OOM issues. This PR improves the situation by estimating the size of the CUDA graphs. It does this by adding a dummy CUDA graph capture with a small dummy KV cache during memory profiling.\n\nPer [discussion](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/30515#issuecomment-3739405494), this functionality is off by default in order not to disturb default `--gpu-memory-utilization` behavior, and may be enabled with `VLLM_MEMORY_PROFILER_ESTIMATE_CUDAGRAPHS=1`\n\n## Test Plan\n```\nvllm serve deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1 \\\n    -dp 8\n    --enable-expert-parallel\n    --gpu-memory-utilization <mem>\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\n\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Improves startup memory accounting by estimating CUDA graph usage and incorporating it into profiling (opt-in via `VLLM_MEMORY_PROFILER_ESTIMATE_CUDAGRAPHS`).\n> \n> - `gpu_model_runner`: adds `profile_cudagraph_memory` to estimate first-capture and per-graph bytes using a minimal `KV` cache, private graph pool, GC freeze, and cleanup; extends `_dummy_run` with `profile_seq_lens`; introduces helpers (`_warmup_and_capture`, `_get_decode_cudagraph_batch_sizes`, `_get_cudagraph_profiling_info`, `_init_minimal_kv_cache_for_profiling`, `_freeze_gc`, `_cleanup_profiling_kv_cache`); defaults empty `cudagraph_batch_sizes`; `capture_model` now returns `(total_bytes, full_bytes)` and clears caches pre/post\n> - `gpu_worker`: during memory profiling, optionally runs CUDA graph estimation, adds first-capture to `peak_activation_memory`, subtracts estimated graph bytes from `available_kv_cache_memory_bytes`, and logs estimated vs actual CUDA graph pool usage\n> - `envs.py`: adds `VLLM_MEMORY_PROFILER_ESTIMATE_CUDAGRAPHS` env var\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit d2d5ca1de0e8ec807d191350a8e6a7f26c0fa9cd. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n",
